{"title": "Arrows of Freethought", "description": "In these 21 short essays, George William Foote shoots \"Arrows of Freethought\" in which he lays down his views on atheism, secularism, and freethought. He talks about religion and progress, explains the gospel of freethought and how literature deals with freethought. He gives a defence of Thomas Paine and explains the views of his contemporaries on atheism. Foote is known as the founder of \"The Freethinker\", a secular humanist magazine that started in 1881 and still exists today. (Summary by Ava)", "duration": 15751, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "349", "name": "George William Foote"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/arrows_of_freethought_2302_librivox/arrowsfreethought_2302.jpg", "copyright_year": "1882", "genres": ["Essays & Short Works", "Atheism & Agnosticism"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Availle"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Availle"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "bdanzige"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface", "readers": [4174], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/arrows_of_freethought_2302_librivox/arrowsoffreethought_00_foote_64kb.mp3", "duration": 113}, {"section": 1, "title": "Religion and Progress", "readers": [10159], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/arrows_of_freethought_2302_librivox/arrowsoffreethought_01_foote_64kb.mp3", "duration": 842}, {"section": 2, "title": "A Defence of Thomas Paine", "readers": [10159], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/arrows_of_freethought_2302_librivox/arrowsoffreethought_02_foote_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1270}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Gospel of Freethought", "readers": [10159], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/arrows_of_freethought_2302_librivox/arrowsoffreethought_03_foote_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1107}, {"section": 4, "title": "Freethought in Current Literature", "readers": [688], "path": "https://www.arch